NarkDB Benchmarks
	by Terark panfengfeng leipeng and fuxinyuan, Jan 2016

In order to test NakrDB's performance, we benchmark it against other well-established database implementations. We compare NarkDB against RocksDB (version 2.5), Redis (version 3.0.6) and WiredTiger (version 2.7.0). 

Benchmarks were all performed on a eight-core Intel(R) Xeon(R) CPU E5-2680 v3 @ 2.50GHz, with 16 GB of DDR3 RAM machine. The OS version is 3.10.0-123.9.3.el7.x86_64.

Benchmark Source Code

We wrote benchmark tools for rocksdb, redis, wiredtiger, narkdb on LevelDB's db_bench. The code for each of the benchmarks resides here:
	RocksDB: doc/bench/db_bench_rocksdb.cc	
	Redis: doc/bench/db_bench_redis.cc	
	Wiredtiger: doc/bench/db_bench_wiredtiger.cc	
	NarkDB: doc/bench/db_bench_nark.cc

1. Baseline Performance

This section gives the baseline performance of all the databases. Following sections show how performance changes as various parameters are varied. For the baseline:
	Using compression
	Kyes are 16 bytes each
	Value are 64 bytes each (with enough redundancy so that a simple compressor shringks them to 50% of their original size)	
	Total data volume is 4GB (no-compression), so that the number of key/value pair is 4GB/80B (~50000000)

Other specfic configuration:
	RocksDB:
		configuration I: Memtable size:64MB, with bloom filter, with cache size(192MB)
		configuration II: Memtable size:64MB with bloom filter, without cache size
		configuration III: Memtable size 64MB without bloom filter, without cache size
		
	WiredTiger:
		configuration I: Memtable size 64MB, with bloom filter, with cache size(192MB)
		configuration II: default configuration, with bloom filter, withtou cache size 
		configuration III: default condifuration, without bloom filter, without cache size
	
	Redis:	??
	
	NarkDB: 
		configuration I: sync_index = false
		configuration II: sync_index = true


###### Baseline Result ######

Random Writes (~50000000)
	RocksDB (II):		11.177 	micros/op
	WiredTiger (I): 	4.384 	micros/op	
	Redis:
	NarkDB (I):		3.2	micros/op		
	NarkDB (II):	 	10.547 	micros/op	

Random Reads  (~25000000)
	RocksDB (II):		34.920  micros/op
	WiredTiger (I): 	128.141 micros/op	
	Redis:
	NarkDB (I):		88.87 	micros/op
	NarkDB (II):		91.982	micros/op
